---
/**
 * rest-api · 0011 · Figure 3 — "Resource model → endpoints" sketch for a
 * payments service API (Customer owns PaymentMethods + Charges; each Charge owns
 * Refunds; endpoints map to methods + status codes).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/rest-api/lessons/0011-mock-interview-whiteboard-design.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the same reason
 * as Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes (and <tspan>) is unreliable
 * inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro. References the shared #arw marker
 * defined by the lesson body's <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A resource sketch for a payments API: Customer owns PaymentMethods and Charges; each Charge owns Refunds; endpoints map to methods and status codes"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">RESOURCE MODEL → ENDPOINTS (THE DATA MODEL IS THE DESIGN)</text
            >

            <!-- resource tree -->
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="34"
                width="150"
                height="40"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="89" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Customer</text
            >
            <text x="89" y="67" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >/v1/customers/{'{'}id{'}'}</text
            >

            <rect x="14" y="100" width="150" height="40" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="89"
                y="118"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">PaymentMethod</text
            >
            <text x="89" y="133" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >card on file</text
            >

            <rect x="14" y="166" width="150" height="40" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
            <text
                x="89"
                y="184"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Charge</text
            >
            <text x="89" y="199" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >/v1/charges/{'{'}id{'}'}</text
            >

            <rect x="200" y="166" width="150" height="40" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="275"
                y="184"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Refund</text
            >
            <text x="275" y="199" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >sub-resource of a charge</text
            >

            <line x1="89" y1="74" x2="89" y2="100" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="89" y1="140" x2="89" y2="166" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="164" y1="186" x2="200" y2="186" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <text x="58" y="92" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">owns</text>
            <text x="182" y="180" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">owns</text>

            <!-- endpoints panel -->
            <rect x="382" y="34" width="250" height="172" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="507"
                y="54"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">ENDPOINTS + STATUS CODES</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="76" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                ><tspan font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a">POST</tspan> /v1/charges → 201 | 202</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="96" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                ><tspan font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a">GET</tspan> /v1/charges/{'{'}id{'}'} → 200 +status</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="116" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                ><tspan font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a">POST</tspan> /v1/refunds → 201</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="132" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417">
                422 over total · 409 if refunded</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="152" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110"
                ><tspan font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a">GET</tspan> /v1/charges?customer=&amp;limit=</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="168" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"> → 200 + cursor page</text>
            <text x="398" y="190" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12">Idempotency-Key on every POST</text
            >
            <text x="398" y="202" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Money = integer minor units, never floats</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Charge is strongly consistent and exactly-once from the caller's view; lists can be
        eventually consistent. Auth is server-to-server.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
